ory path\n\n2. **ContentFile** - Individual content files:\n   - `slug: string` - URL slug identifier\n   - `title: string` - Page title\n   - `content: string` - Raw content (markdown or HTML)\n   - `metadata: Record<string, unknown>` - Custom metadata\n   - `date?: string` - Optional publication date\n   - `tags?: string[]` - Optional tags array\n   - `template?: string` - Optional template name\n\n3. **BuildContext** - Passed through entire build pipeline:\n   - `config: SiteConfig` - Site configuration\n   - `files: ContentFile[]` - All content files\n   - `output: Map<string, string>` - Output path → rendered HTML content\n   - `assets: Map<string, Buffer>` - Output path → binary asset data\n   - `data: Map<string, unknown>` - Shared plugin data store for inter-plugin communication\n\n4. **PluginHooks** - Three lifecycle hooks plugins can implement:\n   - `beforeBuild?(ctx: BuildContext): Promise<void> | void` - Before rendering starts\n   - `transformContent?(file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext): Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile` - Transform individual files\n   - `afterBuild?(ctx: BuildContext): Promise<void> | void` - After rendering completes\n\n5. **Plugin** - Plugin interface:\n   - `name: string` - Plugin identifier\n   - `version: string` - Semantic version\n   - `dependencies: string[]` - Names of plugins this depends on\n   - `hooks: PluginHooks` - Hook implementations\n\n6. **Template** - Template rendering interface:\n   - `name: string` - Template identifier\n   - `render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string` - Render function\n\n---\n\n#### `/workspace/src/core/engine.ts` (lines 1-116)\n\n**BuildEngine Class** - Main orchestrator for the build process\n\nConstructor:\n- `constructor(private config: SiteConfig)`\n\nPrivate fields:\n- `plugins: Plugin[] = []` - Array of registered plugins\n- `templates: Map<string, Template> = new Map()` - Template registry\n\n**Public Methods:**\n\n1. **registerPlugin(plugin: Plugin): void**\n   - Adds a plugin to the build pipeline\n\n2. **registerTemplate(template: Template): void**\n   - Registers a template by name in the Map\n\n3. **resolvePluginOrder(): Plugin[]**\n   - Returns plugins in topological sort order based on dependencies\n   - Uses depth-first search (DFS) with visited/visiting sets\n   - Throws \"Circular dependency detected: {name}\" on cycles\n   - Throws \"Missing dependency: {name} requires {dep}\" on missing deps\n   - Lines 18-48\n\n4. **async build(files: ContentFile[]): Promise<BuildContext>**\n   - Main build orchestration pipeline (lines 50-107):\n     1. Creates BuildContext with copies of files, empty output/assets/data maps\n     2. Resolves plugin order via topological sort\n     3. **beforeBuild phase**: Calls beforeBuild hook on each plugin in order\n     4. **transformContent phase**: For each plugin, apply transformContent hook to all files in sequence\n     5. **Render templates phase**: For each file, renders using template (default or specified), stores in ctx.output with slug.html key\n     6. **afterBuild phase**: Calls afterBuild hook on each plugin in order\n     7. Returns the BuildContext\n\n5. **getPlugins(): Plugin[]**\n   - Returns copy of plugins array\n\n6. **getTemplates(): Map<string, Template>**\n   - Returns copy of templates map\n\n---\n\n#### `/workspace/src/core/templates.ts` (lines 1-42)\n\n**Function: createDefaultTemplate(): Template**\n- Returns Template with name: 'default'\n- HTML structure:\n  ```html\n  <!DOCTYPE html>\n  <html>\n  <head>\n    <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n    <title>${data.title || ''} | ${data.siteTitle || ''}</title>\n  </head>\n  <body>\n    <article>\n      <h1>${data.title || ''}</h1>\n      ${data.date ? `<time>${data.date}</time>` : ''}\n      <div class=\"content\">${content}</div>\n    </article>\n  </body>\n  </html>\n  ```\n\n**Function: createListTemplate(): Template**\n- Returns Template with name: 'list'\n- HTML structure:\n  ```html\n  <!DOCTYPE html>\n  <html>\n  <head>\n    <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n    <title>${data.title || ''} | ${data.siteTitle || ''}</title>\n  </head>\n  <body>\n    <h1>${data.title || ''}</h1>\n    <div class=\"list\">${content}</div>\n  </body>\n  </html>\n  ```\n\n---\n\n### 4. CORE TESTS - `/workspace/tests/core.test.ts` (Lines 1-194)\n\n**15 Test Cases** (all must pass):\n\n1. **registers plugins** - Engine.registerPlugin() adds plugin to list\n2. **registers templates** - Engine.registerTemplate() adds template to map\n3. **builds with default template and renders HTML** - Default template wraps content with proper HTML\n4. **builds with list template and renders list HTML** - List template with <div class=\"list\">\n5. **outputs raw content when no matching template** - Falls back to raw content\n6. **calls plugin beforeBuild hook** - beforeBuild is called during build\n7. **calls plugin transformContent hook to transform files** - transformContent modifies file\n8. **calls plugin afterBuild hook** - afterBuild is called during build\n9. **executes plugins in dependency order** - Topological sort respected (a before b if b depends on a)\n10. **throws on circular dependency** - Error: \"Circular dependency detected: ...\"\n11. **throws on missing dependency** - Error: \"Missing dependency: ...\"\n12. **applies multiple plugins transformContent in order** - Multiple plugins applied sequentially\n13. **provides shared data store in build context** - ctx.data Map works for inter-plugin communication\n14. **retains file metadata through build** - metadata, date, tags preserved through pipeline\n15. **produces empty output for empty file list** - Edge case handling\n\nHelper functions:\n- `makeFile(overrides)` - Creates ContentFile with defaults\n- `makePlugin(overrides)` - Creates Plugin with defaults\n\n---\n\n### 5. PLUGIN TEST FILES - COMPLETE REQUIREMENTS\n\n#### `/workspace/tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts` (Lines 1-90)\n\n**Plugin: createMarkdownExtPlugin()**\n\n**8 Test Cases:**\n\n1. **converts basic markdown to HTML**\n   - Input: '# Hello\\n\\nThis is a **bold** paragraph.'\n   - Output must contain: '<h1>', 'Hello', '<strong>bold</strong>'\n   - Uses marked library for markdown conversion\n\n2. **handles footnotes with [^1] syntax**\n   - Input: 'Some text[^1] here.\\n\\n[^1]: This is the footnote.'\n   - Output must contain: '<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>'\n   - Inline footnote references with superscript links\n\n3. **renders footnote section at bottom of content**\n   - Input: 'Text[^1] and more[^2].\\n\\n[^1]: First note.\\n[^2]: Second note.'\n   - Output must contain: '<section class=\"footnotes\">', '<li id=\"fn-1\">First note.</li>', '<li id=\"fn-2\">Second note.</li>'\n   - Footnotes section with list of all notes\n\n4. **converts :::note container to admonition div**\n   - Input: ':::note\\nThis is a note.\\n:::'\n   - Output must contain: '<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">', 'This is a note.'\n   - Custom container syntax for note admonitions\n\n5. **converts :::warning container to admonition div**\n   - Input: ':::warning\\nBe careful!\\n:::'\n   - Output must contain: '<div class=\"admonition admonition-warning\">', 'Be careful!'\n   - Custom container syntax for warning admonitions\n\n6. **converts :::tip container to admonition div**\n   - Input: ':::tip\\nHelpful hint.\\n:::'\n   - Output must contain: '<div class=\"admonition admonition-tip\">', 'Helpful hint.'\n   - Custom container syntax for tip admonitions\n\n7. **preserves existing HTML in content**\n   - Input: '<div class=\"custom\">Already HTML</div>'\n   - Output must contain: 'Already HTML'\n   - Should not double-process HTML\n\n8. **handles empty content**\n   - Input: ''\n   - Output must be defined (not error)\n   - Edge case handling\n\n**Implementation Requirements:**\n- Uses `transformContent` hook\n- Processes markdown with marked library\n- Implements footnote parsing and rendering\n- Implements admonition container parsing (:::type ... :::)\n- Returns transformed ContentFile\n\n---\n\n#### `/workspace/tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts` (Lines 1-107)\n\n**Plugin: createAssetPipelinePlugin()**\n\n**10 Test Cases:**\n\n1. **rewrites relative image URLs to /assets/ path**\n   - Input: '<img src=\"./image.png\" alt=\"test\">'\n   - Output: 'src=\"/assets/image.png\"'\n   - Relative paths converted to absolute /assets/ paths\n\n2. **rewrites relative link URLs to /assets/ path**\n   - Input: '<a href=\"./doc.pdf\">Download</a>'\n   - Output: 'href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\"'\n   - Applies to both img src and a href\n\n3. **leaves absolute URLs unchanged**\n   - Input: '<img src=\"https://cdn.example.com/image.png\">'\n   - Output unchanged: 'src=\"https://cdn.example.com/image.png\"'\n   - External absolute URLs not modified\n\n4. **generates asset manifest in ctx.data**\n   - After transforming file with '<img src=\"./photo.jpg\">'\n   - ctx.data.get('asset-manifest') returns { assets: ['photo.jpg'] }\n   - Stores manifest for other plugins\n\n5. **handles files with no asset references**\n   - Input: '<p>No assets here</p>'\n   - Output unchanged\n   - No error, manifest not created for empty files\n\n6. **handles multiple assets in one file**\n   - Input: '<img src=\"./a.png\"><img src=\"./b.jpg\"><a href=\"./c.pdf\">link</a>'\n   - Manifest contains all three: a.png, b.jpg, c.pdf\n\n7. **asset manifest includes all discovered assets**\n   - Two files processed sequentially\n   - Final manifest has all 2 assets from both files\n   - Accumulates across multiple files\n\n8. **does not double-process already-rewritten URLs**\n   - Input: '<img src=\"/assets/image.png\">'\n   - Output unchanged: 'src=\"/assets/image.png\"'\n   - Already-rewritten paths skipped\n\n9. Implicit: Handles various asset extensions (png, jpg, pdf, etc.)\n\n**Implementation Requirements:**\n- Uses `transformContent` hook\n- Regex to match and rewrite relative URLs in src and href attributes\n- Extracts asset filenames for manifest\n- Updates ctx.data with 'asset-manifest' key containing { assets: string[] }\n- Skips already-rewritten /assets/ paths\n- Returns transformed ContentFile\n\n---\n\n#### `/workspace/tests/plugins/syntax-highlight.test.ts` (Lines 1-107)\n\n**Plugin: createSyntaxHighlightPlugin()**\n\n**9 Test Cases:**\n\n1. **adds language class to code blocks**\n   - Input: '<pre><code class=\"language-javascript\">const x = 1;</code></pre>'\n   - Output: 'class=\"language-javascript highlighted\"'\n   - Adds \"highlighted\" class to language-* classes\n\n2. **adds data-language attribute to pre tags**\n   - Input: '<pre><code class=\"language-python\">print(\"hi\")</code></pre>'\n   - Output: '<pre...data-language=\"python\">...'\n   - Pre tags get data-language attribute extracted from code class\n\n3. **handles multiple code blocks in one file**\n   - Two blocks with language-js and language-py\n   - Both get data-language attributes set correctly\n   - Sequential processing of all blocks\n\n4. **handles code block with no language specified**\n   - Input: '<pre><code>plain code</code></pre>'\n   - Output unchanged: '<pre><code>plain code</code></pre>'\n   - No highlighted class or data-language added\n   - Only processes blocks with language- prefix\n\n5. **adds highlighted class to processed blocks**\n   - Input: '<pre><code class=\"language-rust\">fn main() {}</code></pre>'\n   - Output contains: 'highlighted'\n   - Marks processed blocks\n\n6. **preserves code block content**\n   - Input: '<pre><code class=\"language-ts\">const x: number = 42;</code></pre>'\n   - Output contains: 'const x: number = 42;'\n   - Inner content not modified\n\n7. **handles empty code blocks**\n   - Input: '<pre><code class=\"language-js\"></code></pre>'\n   - Output contains: 'data-language=\"js\"' and 'highlighted'\n   - Works with empty blocks\n\n8. **does not modify inline code**\n   - Input: '<p>Use <code>console.log()</code> for debugging.</p>'\n   - Output unchanged\n   - Only processes <pre><code> blocks, not inline <code>\n\n9. Implicit: Extracts language from class=\"language-{lang}\" pattern\n\n**Implementation Requirements:**\n- Uses `transformContent` hook\n- Regex to find <pre><code class=\"language-XXX\">...code...</code></pre> patterns\n- Adds \"highlighted\" class to the <code> tag\n- Adds data-language=\"XXX\" attribute to parent <pre> tag\n- Does not modify blocks without language class or inline <code> tags\n- Returns transformed ContentFile\n\n---\n\n#### `/workspace/tests/plugins/taxonomy.test.ts` (Lines 1-126)\n\n**Plugin: createTaxonomyPlugin()**\n\n**9 Test Cases:**\n\n1. **builds tag index from file tags**\n   - Files: [{ tags: ['javascript', 'node'] }, { tags: ['javascript'] }]\n   - ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags') is a Map<string, ContentFile[]>\n   - taxonomy-tags.get('javascript') has length 2\n   - taxonomy-tags.get('node') has length 1\n\n2. **generates tag listing pages in ctx.output**\n   - Creates HTML pages like 'tags/javascript.html'\n   - Page content contains titles of all files with that tag ('Post 1')\n   - Generated in afterBuild phase\n\n3. **handles files with no tags**\n   - File without tags property\n   - taxonomy-tags Map remains empty\n\n4. **handles files with multiple tags**\n   - File with tags: ['js', 'node', 'web']\n   - taxonomy-tags.size === 3\n   - All three tags present in map\n\n5. **tag pages list all files with that tag**\n   - Two files with tag 'tech'\n   - tags/tech.html contains both 'First Post' and 'Second Post'\n   - Lists all files for a given tag\n\n6. **stores tag map in ctx.data**\n   - ctx.data.has('taxonomy-tags') is true\n   - Used by other plugins (rss-feed, sitemap)\n\n7. **handles empty file list**\n   - Empty files array\n   - taxonomy-tags.size === 0\n   - No error\n\n8. **tags are case-normalized to lowercase**\n   - Files with tags: ['JavaScript'] and ['JAVASCRIPT']\n   - taxonomy-tags.has('javascript') is true (lowercase)\n   - taxonomy-tags.get('javascript').length === 2\n   - Both